text: Shorting protects wealth. Buying (and establishing longs) creates wealth.
Mark Respectfully... the only thing we have learned from history is that we haven't learned from history topforeignstocks.com/2021/05…
Market views are like butts - everyone has one, Michael.
well done. "Everyone has a plan until you are punched in the mouth." (Mike Tyson)

Consider some of the most respected strategists today (who are bullish)... few anticipated The Great Decession (2007-09) or the Feb/March 2020 market schmessing. For that matter most failed to see March 2009 as a Generational Bottom in Equities.
The evolution from active to passive investing (ETFs, risk parity, etc.) has had profound impact on market prices, volatility and momentum.

"Price has a way of changing sentiment" h/t @hmeisler - 'group stink' and the comfort of crowds/herds dominates thinking, mike. Investment managers are concerned about the business risk of markedly deviating from consensus and quant strategies worship at the altar of price.
Lesson #11 in my 50 Lessons of Investing... * Beware when perennial bulls become bears and beware when perennial bears become bulls.
@tomkeene There is "going going gone" and then there is this... 455 feet.
